SIMPLE: servitor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Servitor
<hw>Serv"i*tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>servire</ets> to serve: cf. F. <ets>serviteur</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who serves; a servant; an attendant; one who acts
under another; a follower or adherent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Your trusty and most valiant <qex>servitor</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Univ. of Oxford, Eng.)</fld> <def>An undergraduate,
partly supported by the college funds, whose duty it formerly was to
wait at table. A <xex>servitor</xex> corresponded to a <xex>sizar</xex>
in Cambridge and Dublin universities.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Servitorship</ent>⟦br⟧
